<h2>Code View</h2>
<p>
    Renders <strong>syntax-highlighted component source</strong> with a <strong>copy</strong> affordance — the
    source-code-view feature from the workbench inventory
    (<a href="/backlog/625-inventory-the-full-feature-surface-across-workbench-tools/">#625</a>), ratified by
    <a href="/backlog/626-map-workbench-features-to-we-standards-which-intents-blocks-a/">#626</a> as a forced block
    mint. It feeds the Web Docs component-catalog surface
    (<a href="/backlog/627-assemble-the-web-docs-component-catalog-surface-from-the-der/">#627</a>) alongside the
    <a href="/blocks/story-canvas/">story-canvas</a> and props-table blocks.
</p>

<h3>Native-first highlighting</h3>
<p>
    The default highlighter paints token ranges with the
    <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CSS_Custom_Highlight_API">CSS Custom Highlight API</a>
    over a tokenizer — registering a <code>Highlight</code> per token class styled with <code>::highlight()</code> —
    rather than wrapping every token in a <code>&lt;span&gt;</code>. The source stays a single, selectable, copyable
    text node. Library highlighters (Prism, Shiki, highlight.js) are <strong>opt-in adapters</strong>, not the baseline.
</p>

<h3>Copy is the shared intent</h3>
<p>
    The copy button composes the <a href="/intents/data-transfer/">data-transfer</a> copy intent (the copy-out / emit
    half), so the affordance — effect, accessibility, and fallbacks — is consistent with every other copy surface
    rather than a bespoke <code>navigator.clipboard</code> call.
</p>

<h3>Usage</h3>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;code-view language="html" copyable&gt;
  &lt;drop-list options="@countries"&gt;&lt;/drop-list&gt;
&lt;/code-view&gt;</code></pre>

<h3>Contract</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Input:</strong> the source as text content (or a <code>src</code>/<code>code</code> property), plus a
        <code>language</code> hint for the tokenizer.</li>
    <li><strong>Copy:</strong> a <code>copyable</code> affordance that writes the verbatim source via the data-transfer
        copy-out half.</li>
    <li><strong>Out of scope:</strong> a live-editable sandbox embed — that is the assembler / playground concern
        (<a href="/backlog/646-devtools-composition-assembler-build-your-own-component-for-/">#646</a>).</li>
    <li><strong>Exports:</strong> <code>CodeViewElement</code>, <code>registerCodeView</code>.</li>
</ul>
